00:29:12.560 --> 00:29:14.919
Uh... just a... a tent.

260
00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:17.519
Moe found us somewhere
but I can't go back there.

261
00:29:17.520 --> 00:29:19.799
How do I know
you are not going to kill me?

262
00:29:19.800 --> 00:29:23.760
You help us and we will help you.

263
00:29:27.000 --> 00:29:29.719
Just tell me what you saw?

264
00:29:29.720 --> 00:29:33.279
I saw the guy that shot
Sean Wallace. I recognise him.

265
00:29:33.280 --> 00:29:36.119
He lives in a place
near where I sleep.

266
00:29:36.120 --> 00:29:38.279
Take me.
Please. I told you what I know.

267
00:29:38.280 --> 00:29:40.199
Yeah. but now I have to find out
if it's true.

268
00:29:40.200 --> 00:29:43.720
- Please. he's gonna kill me.
- Yo. - Please. please!

269
00:29:50.520 --> 00:29:53.079
Armed police! Do not move!
Evening. fellas.

270
00:29:53.080 --> 00:29:56.359
- What's all this fuss about? Don't move.
- Oh!

271
00:29:56.360 --> 00:29:59.240
Hey. let's just calm down. yeah?
Whoa!

272
00:30:00.160 --> 00:30:03.399
- Put your hands on the car. - What for?
- - Do it now. - Don't touch me. - What for?

273
00:30:03.400 --> 00:30:06.120
- Hey!
- Get off me. man. I ain't got nothing.

274
00:30:11.720 --> 00:30:14.039
Elliot Carter... Arh!
You are under arrest

275
00:30:14.040 --> 00:30:16.759
for possession of a firearm
with intent to cause violence.

276
00:30:16.760 --> 00:30:18.879
They're all clear. sir.

277
00:30:18.880 --> 00:30:20.800
Sab! Saba!

278
00:30:21.720 --> 00:30:24.680
- Stay back!
- Get him talking. Find out what I need to know.

279
00:30:29.800 --> 00:30:31.600
Saba?

280
00:31:38.800 --> 00:31:40.600
Hm.

281
00:33:18.680 --> 00:33:20.680
Through here.

282
00:33:30.800 --> 00:33:33.239
I want my phone call.
Lines are busy. mate.

283
00:33:33.240 --> 00:33:34.600
Sorry.

284
00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:06.679
Why did you call me here. Eddie?

285
00:34:06.680 --> 00:34:09.079
You've had your pound of flesh...

286
00:34:09.080 --> 00:34:13.240
- but this ends now.
- No. Not until I've got Billy and Cornelius.

287
00:34:14.080 --> 00:34:16.479
You think Marian's
going to stand for that?

288
00:34:16.480 --> 00:34:20.600
Marian knows what will happen
if she will interfere.

289
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:24.760
Luan. you don't want a war.
None of us do.

290
00:34:26.040 --> 00:34:28.359
I'm thinking of my family.
So am I.

291
00:34:28.360 --> 00:34:31.040
Let it go. Luan. It's done.

292
00:36:08.280 --> 00:36:10.280
Oh. my boy.

293
00:36:16.680 --> 00:36:18.239
Oh. your hands.

294
00:37:02.760 --> 00:37:04.559
Billy.

295
00:37:04.560 --> 00:37:06.600
What the fuck do you want then?

296
00:37:07.920 --> 00:37:09.799
Been a few years. eh. sis?

297
00:37:09.800 --> 00:37:11.600
Long time.

298
00:37:12.760 --> 00:37:15.519
Didn't know family
was so important to you.

299
00:37:15.520 --> 00:37:19.520
Always has been.
It's you that forgot.

300
00:37:24.720 --> 00:37:27.679
Luan thinks you're to blame
for his daughter's death

301
00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:29.599
and he wants you dead.

302
00:37:29.600 --> 00:37:31.519
I can offer you protection.

303
00:37:31.520 --> 00:37:34.680
But I want you to help me
destroy those who murdered Sean.

304
00:37:38.600 --> 00:37:41.239
Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
Billy. Billy.

305
00:37:41.240 --> 00:37:44.960
Are you fucking joking?
You're the one who left him to die.

306
00:37:46.120 --> 00:37:48.439
Why don't you just say it?

307
00:37:48.440 --> 00:37:52.640
For once.
admit that you made a mistake.

308
00:37:54.120 --> 00:37:57.320
Admit that you abandoned us.
both of us.

309
00:37:58.120 --> 00:38:01.040
Billy. your mother's right.

310
00:38:02.320 --> 00:38:05.399
You can stand here all-night
tearing strips off each other

311
00:38:05.400 --> 00:38:07.559
but fact of the matter is.
Sean's dead...

312
00:38:07.560 --> 00:38:10.280
and the cunts that framed us aren't.

313
00:38:11.040 --> 00:38:14.039
The only way for you
to get justice for your brother now

314
00:38:14.040 --> 00:38:16.080
is for us to work together.

315
00:38:16.760 --> 00:38:19.400
You can blow each other's brains out
after that.

316
00:39:14.840 --> 00:39:16.159
Oi oi!

317
00:39:16.160 --> 00:39:18.080
Hello?!

318
00:39:18.760 --> 00:39:21.040
I want my fucking phone call!

319
00:39:47.120 --> 00:39:48.920
Hey!

320
00:39:51.280 --> 00:39:53.279
Boss man. know a guy called Ali?

321
00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:55.080
Nah? You sure? Thanks.

322
00:40:09.800 --> 00:40:12.119
I didn't tell them anything.

323
00:40:12.120 --> 00:40:14.400
I swear. man. I didn't.

324
00:40:15.360 --> 00:40:17.319
I didn't. Please.

325
00:40:42.400 --> 00:40:43.680
Shit.

326
00:40:58.040 --> 00:40:59.879
Who's that?

327
00:40:59.880 --> 00:41:03.160
He was dead
when we found him. Throat slit.

328
00:41:06.400 --> 00:41:08.400
What do you want me to do?

329
00:41:09.280 --> 00:41:11.079
Go dark. Look after yourself.

330
00:41:11.080 --> 00:41:12.560
I'll be in touch.

331
00:41:18.040 --> 00:41:20.760
Tell Simone Thearle
I'm ready to talk.

332
00:41:42.880 --> 00:41:44.959
I need to talk to you...

333
00:41:44.960 --> 00:41:46.719
privately.

334
00:41:46.720 --> 00:41:49.360
Yeah. I'm afraid
that's not something I can do.

335
00:41:50.040 --> 00:41:52.159
And even if it was...

336
00:41:52.160 --> 00:41:55.279
Locking me up is pointless.
I wouldn't say that.

337
00:41:55.280 --> 00:41:57.840
They tell me
that firearm possession is um...

338
00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:01.759
- it's a good ten years.
- But I'm not the one you're looking for.

339
00:42:01.760 --> 00:42:05.919
- Mm.
- And if you keep me locked up in here. you may never find them.

340
00:42:05.920 --> 00:42:08.599
And what's going on out there
can only get worse.

341
00:42:08.600 --> 00:42:11.320
Last night.
someone murdered Sean Wallace.

342
00:42:12.160 --> 00:42:15.839
That person is involved
in swapping one ton of clean cocaine

343
00:42:15.840 --> 00:42:18.079
for a product laced with fentanyl.

344
00:42:18.080 --> 00:42:21.559
That product made its way into the
streets and killed 600 people.

345
00:42:21.560 --> 00:42:23.720
And why would this "someone"
do that?

346
00:42:24.480 --> 00:42:26.479
That's what I'm trying to figure out.

347
00:42:26.480 --> 00:42:28.879
An operation that big.
they're not working alone.

348
00:42:28.880 --> 00:42:32.159
You find that clean cocaine.
you find the people that did this.

349
00:42:32.160 --> 00:42:34.559
So you think they've got
your clean cocaine and what.

350
00:42:34.560 --> 00:42:36.120
planning to sell it?

351
00:42:37.600 --> 00:42:40.640
I'm just a concerned citizen.
OK.

352
00:42:42.600 --> 00:42:44.400
I've read about you too.

353
00:42:46.040 --> 00:42:47.639
OK.

354
00:42:47.640 --> 00:42:49.680
I know about your brother.

355
00:42:52.000 --> 00:42:53.320
I've lost people also.

356
00:42:54.600 --> 00:42:57.360
And I know how much
you want to make a change.

357
00:43:04.200 --> 00:43:06.200
We can help each other.

358
00:43:09.640 --> 00:43:11.640
We have a deal?

359
00:43:43.840 --> 00:43:45.720
Come forward.

360
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:49.520
Stop there.

361
00:43:52.440 --> 00:43:54.440
Licence. please.

362
00:43:57.480 --> 00:43:59.039
Thank you.

363
00:43:59.040 --> 00:44:01.719
What is this?
Random spot checks.

364
00:44:01.720 --> 00:44:04.679
Part of the mayor's
new war on drugs.

365
00:44:04.680 --> 00:44:07.280
Thank you. I need to check the back.

366
00:44:08.760 --> 00:44:11.440
- Excuse me.
- I need to see in the back of the van.

367
00:44:31.200 --> 00:44:32.720
All good. Yeah.

368
00:44:50.000 --> 00:44:52.479
This is your confession.

369
00:44:52.480 --> 00:44:57.319
You sign and date it
for a week's time.

370
00:44:57.320 --> 00:45:00.840
And if you don't deliver by then.
you're back inside.

371
00:45:02.160 --> 00:45:04.080
And you're not getting out.

372
00:45:13.560 --> 00:45:16.360
My release needs to go
through the Dumani lawyers.

373
00:45:17.360 --> 00:45:21.279
This has to look real...
for both of us.

374
00:45:21.280 --> 00:45:23.199
Oh. I'm aware.

375
00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:26.760
- My entire political career.
- Rests on this. - And my life.

376
00:45:27.440 --> 00:45:30.000
Then you'd better
come up with something quick.

377
00:45:43.680 --> 00:45:45.999
The coke's in Belgian beer kegs.

378
00:45:46.000 --> 00:45:48.040
That's what we're looking for.

379
